m_q.target_metric: best starting position (lowest Start value) for each car across all years
sub_questions: Which car number had the best starting position?
What was the actual best starting position value?
In which year did each car achieve its best starting position?

scale_issues: Year column is object type but contains year values - should be integer
Retired column contains categorical status values

format_notes: Year column stored as object instead of numeric

constraints: Start values should be positive integers (grid positions)
Start values should be less than or equal to total cars in race
Best starting position means minimum Start value (position 1 is best)
derived_filters: Filter to find minimum Start value per Car
Consider only races where car actually started (Start not null)
statistical_tests: Check for outliers in Start positions
Verify Start values are within reasonable range (1-33 typical for Indy 500)
output_format_requirements: Should show Car number and its best Start position
Include Year when best Start was achieved
Sort by best Start position ascending
